<TITLE> Kushtia AL leader detained with AK-47 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, November 02 (bdnews24.com) - Police arrested a local Mahila Awami League leader in Kushtia with an AK-47 assault rifle and ammunition on Monday night. Superintendent of Kushtia police Shahabuddin Khan told bdnews24.com, "A police checkpost at Managalbaria stopped a microbus heading towards Kushtia town at around 11pm." He said the microbus was carrying Taslima Khanam Akhi, secretary of a local Mahila Awami League committee. "She was arrested after an AK-47 rifle, a shotgun and 82 rounds of ammunition were recovered from the vehicle," said Khan. Kushtia Sadar police chief SM Faruque said of the 82 rounds of ammo, 66 rounds were for the AK-47 and 16 for the shotgun. Three others were arrested with Akhi, identified as co-passengers 'Rani' and 'Razzak' and microbus driver 'Shahin'. Awami League's Kushtia town secretary, Amirul Islam, told bdnews24.com Akhi was a former commissioner of Kushtia municipality's Ward No 8. He said she was now secretary of "one faction" of Kushtia town's Mahila Awami League committee. He gave no comment about the arrest. bdn
